"Abstract Picture the scene: you’re just leaving your house for work in the morning and before setting off you run a quick security check. All windows are closed, the back door is shut and the alarm set before you double lock the front door. You then place the front door key under the welcome mat with a sign saying ‘look under here’. This is what thousands of organizations are doing by failing to monitor and manage their user IDs effectively, because they are the technology equivalent of a master key to your network systems."
